  "text": "It can be also observed in Figure 6 that lower molecular weight resins (mPE2 and LDPE) provide larger increase of the entrance pressure loss than the high molecular weight polyethylenes (mPE1 and znHDPE). For example, at 45 wt% filler loading mPE2 resin (MI = 4 g/10 min) provides almost 10 times increase of the relative entrance pressure loss whereas in the case of mPE1 (MI = 0.35 g/10 min) the increase is only about 3 times. This is probably due to the better wetting of the wood flour particles by the lower viscous melt as suggested by Balasuriya et al. [CITATION_1] .",
